'''Alvaro Salas''' (born May 25, 1953 in Montevideo, Uruguay) is a Uruguayan Master [[Candombe]] drummer and percussion teacher.<ref>[http://www.miami.edu/frost/index.php/frost/frost_events/frost_concert_jazz_band-5/Frost Concert Jazz Band—Huracándombe]</ref>
==Early life== Salas was born in Ansina, a neighbourhood in Palermo, [[Montevideo]].
==Career in music industry== Salas has worked, both live and on records, with a number of musicians, including [[Eduardo Mateo]], Jorginho Gularte, Roberto Galletti, Federico Britos, and Urbano Moraes. He has also worked as a percussionist, arranger, and director with several award-winning Carnival groups including Marabunta, Sueno del Buceo, Vendaval, and others.<ref>[http://carnavaldeluruguay.com/todos-los-ganadores-del-concurso-de-carnaval/. Carnival Contest Winners]</ref> He is the current Director of Afro-Uruguayan social organization Mundo Afro.<ref>[http://www.iaf.gov/resources/publications/grassroots-development-journal/2007-african-descendants-and-development/uruguay-s-organizaciones-mundo-afro URUGUAY’S ORGANIZACIONES MUNDO AFRO]</ref> As well, he runs the musical school in this institution, which has international prestige.<ref>[http://scholarlyrepository.miami.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=2035&context=oa_dissertations Contextualizing Uruguayan Identity Through AfroUruguayan Rhythm]</ref>
